identity disorder exists.

177
00:12:55,321 --> 00:12:58,552
What we witnessed meets the criteria
established in the D.S.M.-IV.

178
00:12:58,624 --> 00:13:01,024
The presence of two or more
distinct personality states...

179
00:13:01,094 --> 00:13:02,959
that recurrently
take control over behavior,

180
00:13:03,029 --> 00:13:05,259
including the protector
identity, Sidney.

181
00:13:05,331 --> 00:13:07,424
The inability to recall
important personal information.

182
00:13:07,500 --> 00:13:09,434
She couldn't recall
her own home town.

183
00:13:09,502 --> 00:13:11,436
Transitions from one
personality state to another...

184
00:13:11,504 --> 00:13:14,940
are usually a matter of seconds and are
often caused by psychosocial stress.

185
00:13:15,007 --> 00:13:18,443
Sidney appeared when we mentioned
that children had been abused.

186
00:13:18,511 --> 00:13:22,072
- But you remain unconvinced ?
- I believe the disorder exists,

187
00:13:22,181 --> 00:13:24,741
but under these circumstances,
I would have to know more.

188
00:13:24,851 --> 00:13:27,684
If Melissa has multiple
personalities, would her--

189
00:13:27,753 --> 00:13:31,189
his testimony
even be admissible ?

190
00:13:31,257 --> 00:13:34,249
Judicial precedents have
established that dissociative
personalities are responsible.

191
00:13:34,327 --> 00:13:36,761
Yes, but we are responsible
for Melissa Riedal.

192
00:13:36,829 --> 00:13:40,526
