Hamilton County to meet the troops,

233
00:19:04,990 --> 00:19:08,255
but... in actuality,

234
00:19:08,327 --> 00:19:10,659
I was searching for him,

235
00:19:10,729 --> 00:19:14,290
knowing that he would attempt
to remain in Tennessee...

236
00:19:14,400 --> 00:19:16,800
rather than retreat
to Dalton.

237
00:19:18,003 --> 00:19:20,130
I found him here...

238
00:19:20,206 --> 00:19:23,004
amongst the others
who had been lost...

239
00:19:23,075 --> 00:19:27,512
as General Thomas pushed
through the Confederate line.

240
00:19:30,783 --> 00:19:34,844
The federal troops would
appear from that direction.

241
00:19:34,920 --> 00:19:38,879
Rather than retreat any further,
they fought them,

242
00:19:38,958 --> 00:19:42,155
hiding us in the bunker.

243
00:19:42,228 --> 00:19:46,028
Inside,
I could smell the smoke,

244
00:19:46,131 --> 00:19:49,794
hear the rifles,

245
00:19:49,902 --> 00:19:54,202
feel the bodies as they dropped
onto the ground above.

246
00:19:57,877 --> 00:20:01,244
Every last one.

247
00:20:04,350 --> 00:20:09,515
26th of November, 1863.

248
00:20:17,796 --> 00:20:19,787
I was here...

249
00:20:22,067 --> 00:20:23,659
as were you.

250
00:20:32,912 --> 00:20:37,474
This is the field
where I watched you die.

251
00:20:54,066 --> 00:20:56,091
[Scully]
Who are you calling ?

252
00:20:56,168 --> 00:20:58,932
I'm arranging for a therapist trained in
hypnosis to be at the command center.

253
00:20:59,004 --> 00:21:02,098
Because hypnosis is used in the
treatment of dissociative identities...

254
00:21:02,174 --> 00:21:05,473
to bring forth a patient's
various personalities ?

255
00:21:05,544 --> 00:21:08,775
She wants to talk, Scully.
It's a matter of getting it out of her.

256
00:21:08,881 --> 00:21:11,873
No, it's about regressing her
to a past life.

257
00:21:11,984 --> 00:21:17,047
Don't do this to her, Mulder.
This poor woman's mind,
her life is in shreds.

258
00:21:17,122 --> 00:21:21,081
Just being married to Ephesian indicates
she is susceptible to suggestion.

259
00:21:21,160 --> 00:21:24,220
You-You were there, Scully !

260
00:21:24,296 --> 00:21:28,596
You saw it. You heard it.
Why can't you feel it ?

261
00:21:28,667 --> 00:21:32,797
How could I know about a bunker
in a field where I've never been ?

262
00:21:32,871 --> 00:21:36,864
And why is it that Vernon Ephesian is,
reported by you, a paranoid sociopath...

263
00:21:36,942 --> 00:21:39,536
because he believes that he lived
in Greece a hundred years ago,

264
00:21:39,645 --> 00:21:42,705
and you're not, even though
you believe you died in that field ?

265
00:21:50,022 --> 00:21:53,082
[Woman]
I'm talking to Melissa.

266
00:21:53,158 --> 00:21:55,922
In the last year, at the Temple
of the Seven Stars,

267
00:21:55,995 --> 00:22:01,092
is there anything that happened that
you thought was wrong, that hurt you ?

268
00:22:01,166 --> 00:22:03,225
Yes.

269
00:22:08,440 --> 00:22:10,635
There was a...

270
00:22:12,811 --> 00:22:16,076
woman
who came to the temple.

271
00:22:17,983 --> 00:22:20,850
She and her son
had been living on the street.

272
00:22:20,919 --> 00:22:24,946
- What was her name ?
- Elizabeth.

273
00:22:25,024 --> 00:22:28,289
Her son was Scott.

274
00:22:28,360 --> 00:22:31,158
Vernon took a liking
to the boy.

275
00:22:31,230 --> 00:22:34,666
He said that he was
a prophet returning.

276
00:22:36,402 --> 00:22:39,098
He took the boy
away from his mother.

277
00:22:39,171 --> 00:22:42,572
[Therapist]
Took him away? How?

278
00:22:42,675 --> 00:22:45,508
Vernon's children are
the grand children of God,

279
00:22:45,577 --> 00:22:48,512
kept separate from the others.

280
00:22:48,580 --> 00:22:51,572
The mother's heart was broken.

281
00:22:51,684 --> 00:22:53,879
She was afraid.

282
00:22:53,952 --> 00:22:56,079
The mighty men--

283
00:22:58,457 --> 00:23:02,757
Late... night...

284
00:23:02,828 --> 00:23:05,490
Liz sneaks in to see Scott.

285
00:23:05,564 --> 00:23:07,828
Oh, he was happy.

286
00:23:07,900 --> 00:23:12,860
She brings him Butterfingers
she stole from the kitchen.

287
00:23:15,574 --> 00:23:21,308
Vernon-- Vernon--
Vernon, catches them.

288
00:23:21,413 --> 00:23:24,940
The mighty men--

289
00:23:25,050 --> 00:23:28,986
They pull her away
and beat her...

290
00:23:29,054 --> 00:23:31,079
in front of her son.

291
00:23:31,156 --> 00:23:33,556
The boy--
" No, no, Mom !"

292
00:23:33,625 --> 00:23:36,560
[Crying]

293
00:23:36,628 --> 00:23:40,189
Vernon-- Vernon--

294
00:23:40,265 --> 00:23:42,597
Vernon pulls him by--

295
00:23:42,668 --> 00:23:46,661
Vernon pulls him by his hair...

296
00:23:46,739 --> 00:23:50,539
pulls down his pajamas,
and hit him.

297
00:23:52,511 --> 00:23:55,639
"You're not a child of God."

298
00:23:55,748 --> 00:23:58,774
"Garbage," he calls him.

299
00:23:58,884 --> 00:24:01,546
He told him to sleep
in the trash...

300
00:24:01,620 --> 00:24:03,747
with the rats.

301
00:24:05,057 --> 00:24:09,118
The mother--
The mother cries,

302
00:24:09,194 --> 00:24:13,927
but Vernon beats him...
in front of her.

303
00:24:13,999 --> 00:24:17,662
[Whimpering]
No, no, no.

304
00:24:17,736 --> 00:24:21,797
[ Sidney] Look !
Brilliant, brilliant, brilliant move !

305
00:24:21,874 --> 00:24:26,641
What do you want to know ?
Just-Just leave Melissa alone.

306
00:24:26,745 --> 00:24:28,713
She doesn't need
to go through that anymore.

307
00:24:28,814 --> 00:24:32,147
- [ Mouths Words ]
- Where are the guns ?

308
00:24:32,217 --> 00:24:35,015
The b-bunkers. Yeah.

309
00:24:35,087 --> 00:24:38,022
The Civil War bunkers.
Vernon-- Vernon--

310
00:24:38,090 --> 00:24:40,058
Vernon and his goons know,
but I don't.

311
00:24:40,125 --> 00:24:44,027
- I really don't.
- Maybe there's a map of
the battlefield in the records.

312
00:24:44,096 --> 00:24:47,088
You know how to find
the other bunkers.

313
00:24:47,166 --> 00:24:49,327
Mulder--

314
00:24:49,401 --> 00:24:51,335
Melissa.

315
00:24:54,373 --> 00:24:56,500
It's me, Melissa.

316
00:24:59,711 --> 00:25:03,044
I want you to go back...

317
00:25:03,115 --> 00:25:05,106
back to the field.

318
00:25:16,795 --> 00:25:19,525
[ Sobs ]

319
00:25:24,336 --> 00:25:26,429
Oh.

320
00:25:29,842 --> 00:25:34,302
[ Southern Accent ]
Your eyes may have changed shade...

321
00:25:34,379 --> 00:25:37,974
but it cannot color
the soul behind them.

322
00:25:39,284 --> 00:25:41,582
We have come together
in this life, this time...

323
00:25:43,055 --> 00:25:46,149
only to meet in passing.

324
00:25:50,062 --> 00:25:53,520
It is so heart breaking to wait.

325
00:25:53,599 --> 00:25:57,160
[Crying Softly]

326
00:25:57,236 --> 00:25:59,602
I miss you.

327
00:26:15,220 --> 00:26:18,053
Mulder, this is
a product of her illness.

328
00:26:18,123 --> 00:26:20,353
She couldn't answer
the question on the battlefield.

329
00:26:20,425 --> 00:26:22,689
She gave us no specific names,

330
00:26:22,761 --> 00:26:25,355
no information
to prove her validity.

331
00:26:25,430 --> 00:26:28,422
There is nothing we can use
to prove this is the truth.

332
00:26:28,500 --> 00:26:32,527
- There's one way.
- Mulder, Ephesian's
arraignment is in two hours.

333
00:26:32,604 --> 00:26:36,438
- There is no time to be doing this.
- Wouldn't you, Scully ?

334
00:26:38,844 --> 00:26:41,540
Wouldn't anybody ?

335
00:26:42,881 --> 00:26:45,372
[Therapist]
I want you to go into your past,

336
00:26:45,484 --> 00:26:48,317
beyond your life as Fox Mulder.

337
00:26:52,057 --> 00:26:53,991
What do you see ?

338
00:26:54,059 --> 00:26:56,789
[ Moans ]

339
00:27:02,200 --> 00:27:06,864
Ghetto streets.

340
00:27:06,939 --> 00:27:09,464
Shattered glass.

341
00:27:11,743 --> 00:27:14,075
Bodies of the dead.

342
00:27:17,049 --> 00:27:19,279
I'm a woman...

343
00:27:21,386 --> 00:27:23,718
a Jewish woman.

344
00:27:23,789 --> 00:27:26,485
Poland.

345
00:27:28,794 --> 00:27:31,820
My son is with me.

346
00:27:34,566 --> 00:27:38,434
- He is Samantha.
-[Therapist] Samantha ?

347
00:27:38,503 --> 00:27:41,336
I thought Samantha
was your sister.

348
00:27:41,406 --> 00:27:43,670
In this life...

349
00:27:43,742 --> 00:27:46,336
she is my son.

350
00:27:51,750 --> 00:27:53,843
I see my father.

351
00:27:59,491 --> 00:28:02,289
He's dead in the street.

352
00:28:07,766 --> 00:28:09,368
He is Scully.

353
00:28:11,003 --> 00:28:15,599
But now--
He's gone on now.

354
00:28:15,674 --> 00:28:17,665
They're waiting
for us.

355
00:28:17,743 --> 00:28:21,270
The souls...

356
00:28:21,346 --> 00:28:24,804
come back together.

357
00:28:24,916 --> 00:28:27,612
Different...

358
00:28:27,719 --> 00:28:30,051
but always together...

359
00:28:30,122 --> 00:28:34,115
again and again...

360
00:28:34,226 --> 00:28:37,059
to learn.

361
00:28:37,129 --> 00:28:39,859
I can't go to my father.

362
00:28:47,439 --> 00:28:49,373
[ Sighs ]

363
00:28:49,441 --> 00:28:52,535
Gestapo is standing
next to him.

364
00:28:56,715 --> 00:28:59,377
An officer.

365
00:29:02,354 --> 00:29:05,152
He is Cancer Man.

366
00:29:05,223 --> 00:29:08,317
Evil returns as evil.

367
00:29:09,928 --> 00:29:12,362
But love--

368
00:29:12,431 --> 00:29:14,490
Love--

369
00:29:14,566 --> 00:29:18,969
Souls mate eternal.

370
00:29:22,007 --> 00:29:25,101
My husband...

371
00:29:25,177 --> 00:29:28,806
is taken away from me...

372
00:29:28,880 --> 00:29:32,008
to the camps.

373
00:29:32,117 --> 00:29:35,109
He is Melissa.

374
00:29:35,220 --> 00:29:39,020
We're always taken away.

375
00:29:42,694 --> 00:29:45,788
I'm rising.

376
00:29:45,864 --> 00:29:48,765
I'm rising now.

377
00:29:53,105 --> 00:29:55,938
I'm rising now...

378
00:29:56,007 --> 00:29:58,441
high above...

379
00:29:58,510 --> 00:30:01,479
my body...

380
00:30:02,781 --> 00:30:05,341
above the field.

381
00:30:05,450 --> 00:30:07,850
My face is bloody.

382
00:30:10,122 --> 00:30:12,386
Near the bunker.

383
00:30:14,693 --> 00:30:17,719
The Federals are gone.

384
00:30:19,898 --> 00:30:22,833
My sergeant is also dead.

385
00:30:25,537 --> 00:30:27,528
He is Scully.

386
00:30:31,443 --> 00:30:33,843
Sarah holds me.

387
00:30:38,016 --> 00:30:40,951
She is sad.

388
00:30:44,723 --> 00:30:48,659
She is Melissa.

389
00:30:48,760 --> 00:30:52,252
She lives...

390
00:30:52,330 --> 00:30:56,198
near the battle.

391
00:30:56,268 --> 00:30:58,327
Hamilton County.

392
00:30:58,403 --> 00:31:00,428
Her name is Kavanaugh...

393
00:31:00,505 --> 00:31:03,906
Sarah Kavanaugh.

394
00:31:03,975 --> 00:31:07,433
And my name...

395
00:31:07,512 --> 00:31:10,447
is Sullivan Biddle.

396
00:31:15,987 --> 00:31:20,117
She doesn't know.

397
00:31:20,192 --> 00:31:22,990
She doesn't know...

398
00:31:25,197 --> 00:31:29,065
that-that
I'm waiting for her...

399
00:31:34,306 --> 00:31:38,106
that we will live again.

400
00:31:39,578 --> 00:31:42,547
We will live again.

401
00:31:45,483 --> 00:31:50,079
God--
Oh, my soul is tired.

402
00:31:50,188 --> 00:31:53,089
Mulder, it's Scully.

403
00:31:53,158 --> 00:31:55,752
Do you see any bunkers
in the field ?

404
00:31:55,827 --> 00:31:58,762
My soul is tired.

405
00:32:03,001 --> 00:32:05,469
I want to rest.

406
00:33:50,508 --> 00:33:54,274
[Scully] Ephesian's being
taken down to his arraignment.

407
00:33:54,346 --> 00:33:57,543
He and Melissa are going
to be released soon.

408
00:33:57,615 --> 00:34:02,382
Dana... if, um...

409
00:34:02,454 --> 00:34:07,357
early in the four years
we've been working together...

410
00:34:07,425 --> 00:34:12,192
an event occurred that suggested
or somebody told you that...

411
00:34:12,263 --> 00:34:14,424
we'd been friends together...

412
00:34:14,499 --> 00:34:19,300
in other lifetimes...
always...

413
00:34:19,371 --> 00:34:23,000
would it have changed some
of the ways we looked at one another ?

414
00:34:23,108 --> 00:34:26,737
Even if I knew for certain...

415
00:34:26,845 --> 00:34:29,279
I wouldn't change a day.

416
00:34:35,687 --> 00:34:38,247
Well, maybe that Flukeman thing.

417
00:34:38,323 --> 00:34:40,655
I could have lived
without that just fine.

418
00:34:44,262 --> 00:34:48,062
[ Sarah ] We have come together
in this life, this time...

419
00:34:48,133 --> 00:34:50,260
only to meet in passing.

420
00:34:53,037 --> 00:34:56,803
It is so heart breaking
to wait.

421
00:34:56,908 --> 00:34:59,968
[ Sarah Sighing ]

422
00:35:00,078 --> 00:35:03,570
I miss you.

423
00:35:06,217 --> 00:35:10,278
- I don't believe in it.
- Why ?

424
00:35:10,355 --> 00:35:14,621
Those tapes are saying we chose
the lives we live before we're born...

425
00:35:14,692 --> 00:35:16,717
and who we live with.

426
00:35:18,797 --> 00:35:21,265
It's a nice idea.

427
00:35:22,400 --> 00:35:25,665
It's a beautiful idea.

428
00:35:27,572 --> 00:35:29,540
I want to believe.

429
00:35:33,278 --> 00:35:38,580
And if I knew it were true,
I'd want to start over.

430
00:35:38,650 --> 00:35:42,848
- I'd want to end this pointless life.
-Sarah...

431
00:35:42,921 --> 00:35:46,789
if it were true...

432
00:35:46,858 --> 00:35:49,019
no life would be pointless.

433
00:36:00,605 --> 00:36:03,073
[Door Opens]

434
00:36:03,174 --> 00:36:07,770
Melissa...
it's time to leave.

435
00:36:22,494 --> 00:36:25,429
[Man]
Get out of here.

436
00:36:31,936 --> 00:36:34,996
